definition.value: The role of a company as a creator of detection instrumentation.
Bandwidth is the range of wavelength of light that it allows to pass through the filter, which is either excitation or emission type.
This categorizes the distinct roles played by antibodies in recognizing either the antigen or an antibody itself.
The role of an antibody to detect and bind a specific antigen in a sample (cell, tissue, protein blot).
The role of an antibody to detect and bind a primary antibody in a sample (cell, tissue, protein blot).

A quality of a protein that harbors a variation from the native protein (called canonical form), which could arise due to alternative promoter usage, alternative splicing, alternative translation initiation and ribosomal frameshifting.

A gene that performs the role of encoding a reporter protein, which can easily be detected in an assay, e.g., luciferase gene that encodes the luciferase protein. DNA constructs that contain reporter genes are excellent tools to understand regulation of gene expression.
90% reduction of a predefined stimulus. Unit of Measure is always % when normalized to the dynamic range of the assay.
